# SlabHQ — Cursor project rules

This repo powers https://slabhq.fyi — real-time snow / trip intelligence for
Ikon Pass resorts. Hosted free on GitHub Pages + Cloudflare Workers + GitHub
Actions. Owner: @xiaoseanlu.

## Stack & layout

- `index.html` — entire frontend as a single static file (vanilla HTML/CSS/JS,
  Leaflet, no build step). This is the main artifact GitHub Pages serves.
- `CNAME` — must stay as `slabhq.fyi`. Don't remove or rename.
- `.nojekyll` — must stay (disables Jekyll on Pages). Don't remove.
- `worker/` — Cloudflare Worker for email subscription (`wrangler.toml`,
  `subscribe-worker.js`). Deployed separately via `npx wrangler deploy`.
- `scripts/check-snow-and-notify.js` — Node script run by GitHub Actions cron
  (6am PST daily) to send powder / storm / epic alerts via Resend.
- `.github/workflows/snow-alert.yml` — the cron workflow.
- `prototypes/` — design explorations; do NOT ship these to Pages.
- `deploy.py` — legacy helper from an older machine; ignore / don't rely on it.

## Local dev

- Frontend: open `index.html` directly, or `npx serve -l 8080 -s` from repo
  root.
- Worker: `cd worker && npx wrangler dev`.
- Alerts script: `node scripts/check-snow-and-notify.js` (needs env vars — see
  `SETUP-EMAIL-ALERTS.md`).
- No `package.json` at the root on purpose — keep the root a zero-build static
  site so GitHub Pages stays trivially reliable.

## Git / collaboration workflow

- Default branch: `main`. Pushing to `main` auto-deploys to
  https://slabhq.fyi via GitHub Pages.
- **Ask before every `git commit` and every `git push`.** Summarize the diff
  first, wait for confirmation, then run.
- Prefer small, focused commits with imperative subjects
  (e.g. `fix: storm window rounding`, `feat: add Niseko resort card`).
- For anything risky (DNS, `CNAME`, workflows, secrets, large `index.html`
  rewrites), open a branch like `change/<topic>` and prepare a PR instead of
  pushing to `main`.

## Things to not do

- Don't add a build step, bundler, or framework to the root app without
  explicit approval — the "single file, zero build" property is a feature.
- Don't commit secrets (Resend keys, Cloudflare tokens, GitHub tokens). They
  live in GitHub Actions secrets and Cloudflare Worker secrets.
- Don't commit `subscribers.json`, `node_modules/`, `.DS_Store`, `.claude/`
  (already gitignored — keep it that way).
- Don't change `CNAME`, `.nojekyll`, or Pages-relevant repo settings without
  flagging it as a deploy-affecting change.
- Don't edit files under `prototypes/` when the task is about the live app.

## When in doubt

Ask. This is a solo side-project that's already live in production, so
reliability > speed.
